All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```ts
// Before (buggy) — stops one short, skipping the last element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — iterates through all elements
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop condition caused the loop to stop at index `items.length - 2`, so the final element was never pushed into `results`. Removing it lets the loop run all the way through the array.

